 need to keep those conflicts in mind.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"jackrabbit-webdav exposes core APIs that depend on the Servlet API, but its POM declares javax.servlet:servlet-api as provided, so normal transitive dependency resolution will not put it on the test compile/runtime classpath.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The library is a WebDAV server/client utility library whose request, response, header, input/output context, and servlet classes use javax.servlet types, while the artifact declares servlet-api with provided scope. Meaningful in-process coverage of those APIs needs the Servlet API available to tests.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or external WebDAV/JCR server is required; documentation describes this artifact as a library, not a deployable server. Keep tests in-process and use simple stubs, mocks, or dynamic proxies for servlet request/response collaborators where needed. No environment variables or system properties were identified as required setup.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact is old and uses pre-Jakarta javax.servlet APIs; do not substitute jakarta.servlet.\",\n    \"SLF4J may warn if no binding is present, but that is not required for meaningful coverage unless tests explicitly assert logging behavior.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04b1dbf2891eeec2016a4239477a448195984961137b0a4048\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1320, "output": 819, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26715, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782724925229, "responseId": "resp_04b1dbf2891eeec2016a42393e223c81